<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE / 2000 4000 and 8000 MODELS BUILT OCTOBER 1, 1998 AND AFTER -
        SPEEDOMETER/TACHOMETER, GAUGES AND WARNING LIGHTS - 9800 - Troubleshooting - ENGINE OIL TEMPERATURE GAUGE,
        SENDER, CIRCUIT AND CLUSTER
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ENGINE OIL TEMPERATURE GAUGE, SENDER, CIRCUIT AND CLUSTER</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08245x_8.xml" xrefid="x0824509">Rear Axle, Engine Oil and Transmission Oil
                    Temperature Gauges
                    <xref refid="x0824509"/>
                </hotlnk>
                for an operation description of the pyrometer system.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Engine Oil Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test</title>
            <para>This test will determine if the gauge is working. It does not determine if the gauge is reading
                accurately.
            </para>
            <table id="t0824515">
                <title>Engine Oil Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.23in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (316) circuit 30 at the oil temperature sender. Does the
                                    gauge read at or below low scale?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(316), 30.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit or gauge possibly defective. Reconnect (316) and go to Engine Oil
                                    Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Use a test lead to jumper connector (316) circuit 30 to ground. Does the gauge
                                    read above full scale?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(316), 30 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit and cluster test good. Reconnect (316) and go to Engine Oil Temperature
                                    Gauge and Sender Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit or gauge possibly defective. Reconnect (316) and go to Engine Oil
                                    Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Engine Oil Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Engine Oil Temperature Gauge and Circuit Quick Test prior to performing this test.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0824516">
                <title>Engine Oil Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.26in"/>
                    <spanspec namest="1" nameend="7" spanname="SPAN1"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect connector (316) from the oil temperature sender. Measure resistance to
                                    ground at circuit 30-G.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(316), 30-G to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit [1]/[2]/[3]*, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove connector. (73) from the gauge cluster. At connector (73) measure
                                    resistance to ground at circuit 30A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 30A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit [1]/[2]/[3]*, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>At the sender connector. (316) use test lead to jumper circuit 30 to 30-G. At
                                    connector. (73) measure resistance to ground at circuit 30A.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), 30A to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit [4]/[5]/[6]/[7]*, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove the oil temperature gauge. Measure resistance between cluster connector
                                    (73) cavity 2 and the gauge ground pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 2, and ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Measure resistance between cluster connector (73) cavity 4, and the gauge sender
                                    pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 4, and sender pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Remove the oil temperature gauge. Measure resistance between cluster connector
                                    (73) cavity 2 and the gauge ground pin
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_27.xml" xrefid="f0824518">(Figure 18)</hotlnk>.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>(73), cavity 2, and ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>&#60;1 ohm.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colname="1">
                                <para>7.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="2">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="3">
                                <para>Turn key on. Measure voltage at oil temperature gauge ignition pin to ground, to
                                    check circuit 28B.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="4">
                                <para>Gauge socket, ignition pin to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="5">
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="6">
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry colname="7">
                                <para>Open in cluster circuit. Replace the gauge cluster.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>8.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure voltage between oil temperature gauge ignition and ground pins, to check
                                    circuit 11-GV/11-GF.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge socket, ignition pin to ground pin.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>12&#177;1.5 volts.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Circuit checks good, Re-install gauge. Go to Engine Oil Temperature Gauge and
                                    Sender Test.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 11-GV/11-GF, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry colspan="7" spanname="SPAN1">
                                <para>*NOTE: [1] - With Cummins N14 and Detroit Diesel Series 60 engines, ground circuit
                                    path is circuit 30-G, connector (340) for Detroit Diesel or (751) for Cummins,
                                    circuit 11-GU.
                                </para>
                                <para>*NOTE: [2] - With a Cummins M11/ISM and Set Forward Axle, ground circuit path is
                                    circuit 30-G, connector (751), circuit 30-GA/11-GJ.
                                </para>
                                <para>*NOTE: [3] - With a Cummins M11/ISM and Set Back Axle, ground circuit path is
                                    circuit 30-G, connector (751), circuit 30-GB/11-GH.
                                </para>
                                <para>*NOTE: [4] - With a Detroit Diesel Series 60 engine, sender circuit path is
                                    circuit 30A/30, connector (338), circuit 30, connector (340), circuit 30.
                                </para>
                                <para>*NOTE: [5] - With a Cummins N14, the sender circuit path is circuit 30A/30,
                                    connector (102), circuit 30, connector (751), circuit 30.
                                </para>
                                <para>*NOTE: [6] - With a Cummins M11/ISM and Set Forward Axle, sender current path is
                                    circuit 30A/30, connector (102), circuit 30/30A, connector (751), circuit 30.
                                </para>
                                <para>*NOTE: [7] - With a Cummins M11/ISM and Set Back Axle, sender current path is
                                    circuit 30A/30, connector (102), circuit 30/30B, connector (751), circuit 30.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Engine Oil Temperature Gauge and Sender Test</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Perform Engine Oil Temperature Gauge Circuit and Cluster Test prior to performing this test
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0824517">
                <title>Engine Oil Temperature Gauge and Sender Test</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="0" rowsep="0">
                    <colspec colname="1" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" colwidth="0.58in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" colwidth="1.54in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" colwidth="0.96in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" colwidth="0.71in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" colwidth="0.92in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" colwidth="1.24in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES- IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect gauge tester ZTSE-2781
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_26.xml" xrefid="f0824516">(Figure 16)</hotlnk>
                                    and
                                    <hotlnk document="s08245x_26.xml" xrefid="f0824517">(Figure 17)</hotlnk>to
                                    connector. (316) circuit 30 and ground. Set to 108 ohms. Does oil temperature gauge
                                    read 220&#176;F (104&#176;C)?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(316), 30 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>108 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry>
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>With gauge tester still connected, set to 35 ohms. Does oil temperature gauge read
                                    320&#176;F (160&#176;C)?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(316), 30 to ground.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>35 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Gauge and circuit check good. Replace sender.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace gauge.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
